{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"alias":"safe-peg-tuner","description":"# Plan-review fidelity-eval harness (semantic: new container path vs baseline findings)\n\n## Why\nS4 (merge G3+G4) and S5 (child bin-packing) change HOW the container LLM calls are made; their \"no fidelity\nregression\" gate needs a SEMANTIC eval comparing REAL LLM findings (merged vs separate; packed vs one-per-call)\nagainst a baseline. The existing parity harness (`rebar.llm.parity` / `workflow/trace.py`) is STRUCTURAL — it runs\nFakeRunner with ZERO model calls and compares decisions/routing, NOT real findings. A new semantic harness is\nrequired to make S4/S5 verifiable. (Opus-review BLOCKER 3.)\n\n## What\n- Capture a CORPUS of real epic plan-reviews (≥5 epics of varied child count/size) as fixtures; the BASELINE is the\n  CURRENT separate-call (G3,G4) / one-child-per-call container findings.\n- Metric: finding RECALL (fraction of baseline container findings reproduced by the candidate path) + G3/G4\n  ATTRIBUTION accuracy (no mis-tagged criterion) + a bound on spurious new findings.\n- Explicit TOLERANCE (e.g. ≥95% finding recall vs baseline AND 0 G3/G4 mis-attributions AND ≤X% new findings),\n  tuned against observed variance.\n- Harness: run a candidate container path over the corpus, diff against the baseline, report pass/fail.\n  Live/billable, OPT-IN (not default CI), documented — like the live round-trip probes.\n\n## Scope\n- In: corpus fixtures, baseline capture, the recall+attribution metric, the tolerance, the diff harness.\n- Out: the merge (S4) / bin-pack (S5) implementations it gates.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] A corpus of ≥5 real epic reviews is captured with baseline container findings recorded as fixtures.\n- [ ] The harness computes finding-recall + G3/G4-attribution-accuracy of a candidate container path vs baseline.\n- [ ] An explicit numeric tolerance is defined + documented; the harness reports pass/fail against it.\n- [ ] The harness is opt-in (not default CI) and documented; `make lint` + tests pass.\n","id":"da34-ac98-e375-4af0","parent_id":"c81c-cbcd-17a0-43d2","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Plan-review fidelity-eval harness (semantic: new container path vs baseline)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1782544895555414001,"uuid":"73ef01f6-d5be-450b-9e47-d50ab632fbc0"}